"fahal","e":"ْlَhَf"},{"b":"6.6","h":"10.55","c":"مِنْ","d":"min","e":"nِm"},{"b":"8.0","h":"11.98","c":"مُدَّكِرٍ","d":"muddakirin","e":"ٍrِkَّdُّm"}],"a":{"g":"And We left it as a sign, so is there any who will remember?"}},"16":{"w":[{"b":"0.03","h":"0.85","c":"فَكَيْفَ","d":"fakayfa","e":"َfْyَkَf"},{"b":"0.82","h":"1.6","c":"كَانَ","d":"kāna","e":"َnāَk"},{"b":"1.4","h":"2.62","c":"عَذَابِي","d":"ʿadhābī","e":"àِbāَhdَʿع"},{"b":"2.7","h":"4.42","c":"وَنُذُرِ","d":"wanudhuri","e":"ِrُhdُnَw"}],"a":{"g":"And how [severe] were My punishment and warning."}},"17":{"w":[{"b":"0.03","h":"0.7","c":"وَلَقَدْ","d":"walaqad","e":"ْdَqَlَw"},{"b":"0.79","h":"1.87","c":"يَسَّرْنَا","d":"yassarnā","e":"āَnْrَّsَy"},{"b":"1.9","h":"3.59","c":"الْقُرْءَانَ","d":"l-qur'āna","e":"َnāَءْrُqْlٱ"},{"b":"3.4","h":"5.74","c":"لِلذِّكْرِ","d":"lildhik'ri","e":"ِrْkِّhdlِl"},{"b":"4.4","h":"7.39","c":"فَهَلْ","d":"fahal","e":"ْlَhَf"},{"b":"5.1","h":"8.55","c":"مِنْ","d":"min","e":"nِm"},{"b":"6.9","h":"10.03","c":"مُدَّكِرٍ","d":"muddakirin","e":"ٍrِkَّdُّm"}],"a":{"g":"And We have certainly made the Qur'an easy for remembrance, so is there any who will remember?","ihya":"<div class='ihya-container' style='margin-top: 20px; padding: 15px; background-color: #f8f9fa; border-left: 4px solid #d4af37; border-radius: 4px;'><h4 style='color: #d4af37; margin-bottom: 15px; font-family: \"Cinzel\", serif;'>Ihya 'Ulum al-Din Commentary</h4><div class='ihya-entry'><span class='badge badge-light' style='color: #666; border: 1px solid #ddd; margin-bottom: 8px;'>Vol1 book 1</span><div class='ihya-text' style='font-size: 1.1em; line-height: 1.6; color: #333;'>Indeed, because it is present within the heart [qalb] yet forgotten due to preoccupation away from it, Allah the Exalted has named all the knowledges [ma'arif] of faith a remembrance [tadhkira]. Thus He, the Exalted, said: \"And We have certainly made the Qur'an easy for remembrance [dhikr]. So is there any who will remember [mudhakir]?\" (54:17). This, then, is the remedy for patience [sabr] from whisperings and preoccupations, and it is the final degree of patience. For indeed, patience from all attachments is a prerequisite for patience from passing thoughts.</div></div><hr style='border-top: 1px dashed #ddd; margin: 15px 0;'><div class='ihya-entry'><span class='badge badge-light' style='color: #666; border: 1px solid #ddd; margin-bottom: 8px;'>Vol4 book2</span><div class='ihya-text' style='font-size: 1.1em; line-height: 1.6; color: #333;'>Indeed, because it is present within the heart [qalb] yet forgotten due to preoccupation away from it, Allah the Exalted has named all the knowledges [ma'arif] of faith a remembrance [tadhkira]. Thus He, the Exalted, said: \"And We have certainly made the Qur'an easy for remembrance [dhikr]. So is there any who will remember [mudhakir]?\" (54:17). This, then, is the remedy for patience [sabr] from whisperings and preoccupations, and it is the final degree of patience. For indeed, patience from all attachments is a prerequisite for patience from passing thoughts.</div></div></div>"}},"18":{"w":[{"b":"0.03","h":"0.85","c":"كَذَّبَتْ","d":"kadhabat","e":"ْtَbَّhdَk"},{"b":"1","h":"2.19","c":"عَادٌ","d":"ʿādun","e":"ٌdāَʿع"},{"b":"2.7","h":"4.01","c":"فَكَيْفَ","d":"fakayfa","e":"َfْyَkَf"},{"b":"3.6","h":"5.44","c":"كَانَ","d":"kāna","e":"َnāَk"},{"b":"4.3","h":"6.47","c":"عَذَابِي","d":"ʿadhābī","e":"àِbāَhdَʿع"},{"b":"5.4","h":"8.65","c":"وَنُذُرِ","d":"wanudhuri","e":"ِrُhdُnَw"}],"a":{"g":"'Aad denied; and how [severe] were My punishment and warning."}},"19":{"w":[{"b":"0.03","h":"0.5","c":"إِنَّا","d":"innā","e":"ٓāَّnِiʾ"},{"b":"1.1","h":"3.19","c":"أَرْسَلْنَا","d":"arsalnā","e":"āَnْlَsْrَaʾ"},{"b":"4.2","h":"5.28","c":"عَلَيْهِمْ","d":"ʿalayhim","e":"ْmِhْyَlَʿع"},{"b":"5.3","h":"7.09","c":"رِيحًا","d":"rīḥan","e":"āًḥyِr"},{"b":"6.8","h":"8.8","c":"صَرْصَرًا","d":"ṣarṣaran","e":"āًrَṣْrَṣ"},{"b":"8.6","h":"10.94","c":"فِي","d":"fī","e":"àِf"},{"b":"9.2","h":"11.73","c":"يَوْمِ","d":"yawmi","e":"ِmْwَy"},{"b":"9.8","h":"12.76","c":"نَحْسٍ","d":"naḥsin","e":"ٍsْḥَn"},{"b":"11.6","h":"14.69","c":"مُسْتَمِرٍّ","d":"mus'tamirrin","e":"ٍّrِmَtْsُّm"}],"a":{"g":"Indeed, We sent upon them a screaming wind on a day of continuous misfortune,","ihya":"<div class='ihya-container' style='margin-top: 20px; padding: 15px; background-color: #f8f9fa; border-left: 4px solid #d4af37; border-radius: 4px;'><h4 style='color: #d4af37; margin-bottom: 15px; font-family: \"Cinzel\", serif;'>Ihya 'Ulum al-Din Commentary</h4><div class='ihya-entry'><span class='badge badge-light' style='color: #666; border: 1px solid #ddd; margin-bottom: 8px;'>j4 k09</span><div class='ihya-text' style='font-size: 1.1em; line-height: 1.6; color: #333;'>And from His signs [ayat] is the subtle air [al-hawa' al-latif], confined between the concave of the sky and the convex of the earth. Its substance is perceived by the sense of touch when the winds blow, yet its form is not seen by the eye. Its totality is like a single sea, and the birds soar in the atmosphere of the sky, racing in swimming through it with their wings, just as the creatures of the sea swim in water. And its sides and its waves are agitated when the winds blow, just as the waves of the sea are agitated. So when God sets the air in motion and makes it a blowing wind, then if He wills, He makes it a herald [nashiran] preceding His mercy, as He, the Glorified, said: 'And We send the fertilizing winds.' Thus, through its motion, the spirit [ruh] of the air reaches the animals and the plants, and they become prepared for growth. And if He wills, He makes it a punishment ['adhab] upon the disobedient from His creation, as God, the Exalted, said: 'Indeed, We sent upon them a screaming wind, on a day of unceasing calamity, plucking the people as if they were trunks of uprooted palm trees.'</div></div><hr style='border-top: 1px dashed #ddd; margin: 15px 0;'><div class='ihya-entry'><span class='badge badge-light' style='color: #666; border: 1px solid #ddd; margin-bottom: 8px;'>j4 k09</span><div class='ihya-text' style='font-size: 1.1em; line-height: 1.6; color: #333;'>And from His signs [ayat] is the subtle air [al-hawa' al-latif], confined between the concave of the sky and the convex of the earth. Its substance is perceived by the sense of touch when the winds blow, yet its form is not seen by the eye. Its totality is like a single sea, and the birds soar in the atmosphere of the sky, racing in swimming through it with their wings, just as the creatures of the sea swim in water. And its sides and its waves are agitated when the winds blow, just as the waves of the sea are agitated. So when God sets the air in motion and makes it a blowing wind, then if He wills, He makes it a herald [nashiran] preceding His mercy, as He, the Glorified, said: 'And We send the fertilizing winds.' Thus, through its motion, the spirit [ruh] of the air reaches the animals and the plants, and they become prepared for growth. And if He wills, He makes it a punishment ['adhab] upon the disobedient from His creation, as God, the Exalted, said: 'Indeed, We sent upon them a screaming wind, on a day of unceasing calamity, plucking the people as if they were trunks of uprooted palm trees.'</div></div></div>"}},"20":{"w":[{"b":"0.03","h":"0.35","c":"تَنْزِعُ","d":"tanziʿu","e":"ُʿعِznَt"},{"b":"1.5","h":"2.23","c":"النَّاسَ","d":"l-nāsa","e":"َsāَّnlٱ"},{"b":"3","h":"3.91","c":"كَأَنَّهُمْ","d":"ka-annahum","e":"ْmُhَّnَaʾَk"},{"b":"5.0","h":"6.23","c":"أَعْجَازُ","d":"aʿjāzu","e":"ُzāَjgْʿعَaʾ"},{"b":"6.1","h":"8.02","c":"نَخْلٍ","d":"nakhlin","e":"ٍlْhkَn"},{"b":"7.6","h":"10.03","c":"مُنْقَعِرٍ","d":"munqaʿirin","e":"ٍrِʿعَqnُّm"}],"a":{"g":"Extracting the people as if they were trunks of palm trees uprooted."}},"21":{"w":[{"b":"0.03","h":"0.85","c":"فَكَيْفَ","d":"fakayfa","e":"َfْyَkَf"},{"b":"0.79","h":"1.95","c":"كَانَ","d":"kāna","e":"َnāَk"},{"b":"1.4","h":"2.94","c":"عَذَابِي","d":"ʿadhābī","e":"àِbāَhdَʿع"},{"b":"2.6","h":"5.02","c":"وَنُذُرِ","d":"wanudhuri","e":"ِrُhdُnَw"}],"a":{"g":"And how [severe] were My punishment and warning."}},"22":{"w":[{"b":"0.03","h":"0.25","c":"وَلَقَدْ","d":"walaqad","e":"ْdَqَlَw"},{"b":"0.78","h":"1.48","c":"يَسَّرْنَا","d":"yassarnā","e":"āَnْrَّsَy"},{"b":"2","h":"3.2","c":"الْقُرْءَانَ","d":"l-qur'āna","e":"َnāَءْrُqْlٱ"},{"b":"3.3","h":"5.44","c":"لِلذِّكْرِ","d":"lildhik'ri","e":"ِrْkِّhdlِl"},{"b":"4.3","h":"7.07","c":"فَهَلْ","d":"fahal","e":"ْlَhَf"},{"b":"5.0","h":"8.21","c":"مِنْ","d":"min","e":"nِm"},{"b":"6.9","h":"10.04","c":"مُدَّكِرٍ","d":"muddakirin","e":"ٍrِkَّdُّm"}],"a":{"g":"And We have certainly made the Qur'an easy for remembrance, so is there any who will remember?"}},"23":{"w":[{"b":"0.03","h":"1","c":"كَذَّبَتْ","d":"kadhabat","e":"ْtَbَّhdَk"},{"b":"0.98","h":"2.37","c":"ثَمُودُ","d":"thamūdu","e":"ُdwُmَht"},{"b":"1.9","h":"4.83","c":"بِالنُّذُرِ","d":"bil-nudhuri","e":"ِrُhdُّnlٱِb"}],"a":{"g":"Thamud denied the warning"}},"24":{"w":[{"b":"0.03","h":"0.2","c":"فَقَالُوا","d":"faqālū","e":"۟āٓwُlāَqَf"},{"b":"2.1","h":"2.55","c":"أَبَشَرًا","d":"abasharan","e":"āًrَhsَbَaʾ"},{"b":"3.0","h":"3.84","c":"مِنَّا","d":"minnā","e":"āَّnِّm"},{"b":"5.2","h":"6.37","c":"وَاحِدًا","d":"wāḥidan","e":"āًdِḥَٰw"},{"b":"6.2","h":"7.72","c":"نَتَّبِعُهُ","d":"nattabiʿuhu","e":"ٓۥُhُʿعِbَّtَّn"},{"b":"10.0","h":"11.65","c":"إِنَّا","d":"innā","e":"ٓāَّnِiʾ"},{"b":"11.2","h":"14.24","c":"إِذًا","d":"idhan","e":"āًhdِiʾ"},{"b":"13.2","h":"14.92","c":"لَفِي","d":"lafī","e":"àِfَّl"},{"b":"14.1","h":"16.3","c":"ضَلَالٍ","d":"ḍalālin","e":"ٍlَٰlَḍ"},{"b":"15.3","h":"18.67","c":"وَسُعُرٍ","d":"wasuʿurin","e":"ٍrُʿعُsَw"}],"a":{"g":"And said, \"Is it one human being among us that we should follow? Indeed, we would then be in error and madness.","ihya":"<div class='ihya-container' style='margin-top: 20px; padding: 15px; background-color: #f8f9fa; border-left: 4px solid #d4af37; border-radius: 4px;'><h4 style='color: #d4af37; margin-bottom: 15px; font-family: \"Cinzel\", serif;'>Ihya 'Ulum al-Din Commentary</h4><div class='ihya-entry'><span class='badge badge-light' style='color: #666; border: 1px solid #ddd; margin-bottom: 8px;'>Vol4 book2</span><div class='ihya-text' style='font-size: 1.1em; line-height: 1.6; color: #333;'>Indeed, \"A human [bashar] from among us, one, shall we follow him?\" So these blindings [al-'amawiyyat] are what prevented the guidance [al-hidaya].</div></div></div>"}},"25":{"w":[{"b":"0.03","h":"0.15","c":"أَءُلْقِيَ","d":"a-ul'qiya","e":"َàِqْlُءَaʾ"},{"b":"1.0","h":"1.84","c":"الذِّكْرُ","d":"l-dhik'ru","e":"ُrْkِّhdlٱ"},{"b":"1.8","h":"2.72","c":"عَلَيْهِ","d":"ʿalayhi","e":"ِhْyَlَʿع"},{"b":"2.7","h":"4.23","c":"مِنْ","d":"min","e":"ۢnِm"},{"b":"3.8","h":"5.18","c":"بَيْنِنَا","d":"bayninā","e":"āَnِnْyَb"},{"b":"4.9","h":"6.94","c":"بَلْ","d":"bal","e":"ْlَb"},{"b":"5.3","h":"7.64","c":"هُوَ","d":"huwa","e":"َwُh"},{"b":"5.8","h":"8.27","c":"كَذَّابٌ","d":"kadhābun","e":"ٌbāَّhdَk"},{"b":"7.1","h":"10.58","c":"أَشِرٌ","d":"ashirun","e":"ٌrِhsَaʾ"}],"a":{"g":"Has the message been sent down upon him from among us? Rather, he is an insolent liar.\""}},"26":{"w":[{"b":"0.03","h":"0.5","c":"سَيَعْلَمُونَ","d":"sayaʿlamūna","e":"َnwُmَlْʿعَyَs"},{"b":"1.6","h":"2.7","c":"غَدًا","d":"ghadan","e":"āًdَغ"},{"b":"1.9","h":"3.34","c":"مَنِ","d":"mani","e":"ِnَّm"},{"b":"3.7","h":"4.5","c":"الْكَذَّابُ","d":"l-kadhābu","e":"ُbāَّhdَkْlٱ"},{"b":"5.1","h":"6.73","c":"الْأَشِرُ","d":"l-ashiru","e":"ُrِhsَaʾْlٱ"}],"a":{"g":"They will know tomorrow who is the insolent liar."}},"27":{"w":[{"b":"0.03","h":"0.4","c":"إِنَّا","d":"innā","e":"āَّnِiʾ"},{"b":"1.5","h":"2.07","c":"مُرْسِلُوا","d":"mur'silū","e":"۟āwُlِsْrُm"},{"b":"2.3","h":"3.67","c":"النَّاقَةِ","d":"l-nāqati","e":"ِẗَqāَّnlٱ"},{"b":"4.1","h":"5.39","c":"فِتْنَةً","d":"fit'natan","e":"ًẗَnْtِf"},{"b":"5.1","h":"6.87","c":"لَهُمْ","d":"lahum","e":"ْmُhَّl"},{"b":"5.9","h":"8.14","c":"فَارْتَقِبْهُمْ",